About Wikipedia

This is the front page of the Simple English Wikipedia. Wikipedias are places where people work together to write encyclopedias in different languages. We use Simple English words and grammar here. The Simple English Wikipedia is for everyone, such as children and adults who are learning English. There are 274,838 articles on the Simple English Wikipedia. All of the pages are free to use. They have all been published under both the Creative Commons Attribution/Share-Alike License 4.0 International License and the GNU Free Documentation License. You can help here! You may change these pages and make new pages. Read the help pages and other good pages to learn how to write pages here. If you need help, you may ask questions at Simple talk.

When writing articles here:

  • Use Basic English words and shorter sentences. This allows people to understand complex terms or phrases.
  • Write good pages. The best encyclopedia pages have useful, well-written information.
  • Use the pages to learn and teach. These pages can help people learn English. You can also use them to make a new Wikipedia to help other people.
  • Simple does not mean short. Writing in Simple English means that simple words are used. It does not mean readers want basic information. Articles do not have to be short to be simple; expand articles, add details, but use basic vocabulary.
  • Be bold! Your article does not have to be perfect, because other editors will fix it and make it better. And most importantly, do not be afraid to start and make articles better yourself.

Selected article

Tropical Storm Barry was a tropical cyclone that grew quickly. It made landfall on Florida in early June 2007. It was the second Atlantic named storm of the 2007 Atlantic hurricane season. Barry formed in the Gulf of Mexico. It moved toward the northeast, and reached top wind speeds of 60 mph (95 km/h). It then weakened and made landfall near Tampa Bay, Florida. Barry quickly weakened after wind shear blew away most of the thunderstorms. Barry moved up the East Coast of the United States and by June 5, it was taken over by a larger storm.

Rain from Barry in the Cuban province of Pinar del Río hurt three people and damaged 55 houses. In Florida, Barry caused heavy rain in an area that had been in drought. Flooding and wet roads killed two people in traffic accidents. Rough seas killed one surfer in Pinellas County, Florida. In Florida and Georgia, the rain helped firefighters fight wildfires. Damage from the storm was minor.

This is the front page of the Simple English Wikipedia. Wikipedias are places where people work together to write encyclopedias in different languages. We use Simple English words and grammar here. The Simple English Wikipedia is for everyone, such as children and adults who are learning English. There are 274,838 articles on the Simple English Wikipedia. All of the pages are free to use. They have all been published under both the Creative Commons Attribution/Share-Alike License 4.0 International License and the GNU Free Documentation License. You can help here! You may change these pages and make new pages. Read the help pages and other good pages to learn how to write pages here. If you need help, you may ask questions at Simple talk.

When writing articles here:

  • Use Basic English words and shorter sentences. This allows people to understand complex terms or phrases.
  • Write good pages. The best encyclopedia pages have useful, well-written information.
  • Use the pages to learn and teach. These pages can help people learn English. You can also use them to make a new Wikipedia to help other people.
  • Simple does not mean short. Writing in Simple English means that simple words are used. It does not mean readers want basic information. Articles do not have to be short to be simple; expand articles, add details, but use basic vocabulary.
  • Be bold! Your article does not have to be perfect, because other editors will fix it and make it better. And most importantly, do not be afraid to start and make articles better yourself.

Selected article

Tropical Storm Barry was a tropical cyclone that grew quickly. It made landfall on Florida in early June 2007. It was the second Atlantic named storm of the 2007 Atlantic hurricane season. Barry formed in the Gulf of Mexico. It moved toward the northeast, and reached top wind speeds of 60 mph (95 km/h). It then weakened and made landfall near Tampa Bay, Florida. Barry quickly weakened after wind shear blew away most of the thunderstorms. Barry moved up the East Coast of the United States and by June 5, it was taken over by a larger storm.

Rain from Barry in the Cuban province of Pinar del Río hurt three people and damaged 55 houses. In Florida, Barry caused heavy rain in an area that had been in drought. Flooding and wet roads killed two people in traffic accidents. Rough seas killed one surfer in Pinellas County, Florida. In Florida and Georgia, the rain helped firefighters fight wildfires. Damage from the storm was minor.

## Selected article
[![](https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/44/Barry_01_jun_2007_1905Z.jpg/120px-Barry_01_jun_2007_1905Z.jpg)](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Barry_01_jun_2007_1905Z.jpg) **[Tropical Storm Barry](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tropical_Storm_Barry_\(2007\) "Tropical Storm Barry \(2007\)")** was a [tropical cyclone](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tropical_cyclone "Tropical cyclone") that grew quickly. It made [landfall](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Landfall_\(meteorology\) "Landfall \(meteorology\)") on [Florida](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florida "Florida") in early June 2007. It was the second [Atlantic](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atlantic_hurricane "Atlantic hurricane") [named storm](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tropical_cyclone "Tropical cyclone") of the [2007 Atlantic hurricane season](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/2007_Atlantic_hurricane_season "2007 Atlantic hurricane season"). Barry formed in the [Gulf of Mexico](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gulf_of_Mexico "Gulf of Mexico"). It moved toward the northeast, and reached top wind speeds of 60 [mph](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_per_hour "Miles per hour") (95 km/h). It then weakened and made landfall near Tampa Bay, [Florida](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florida "Florida"). Barry quickly weakened after [wind shear](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wind_shear "Wind shear") blew away most of the [thunderstorms](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thunderstorm "Thunderstorm"). Barry moved up the [East Coast of the United States](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/East_Coast_of_the_United_States "East Coast of the United States") and by June 5, it was taken over by a larger storm.  Rain from Barry in the [Cuban](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cuba "Cuba") province of [Pinar del Río](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pinar_del_R%C3%ADo_Province "Pinar del Río Province") hurt three people and damaged 55 houses. In Florida, Barry caused heavy rain in an area that had been in [drought](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drought "Drought"). [Flooding](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flood "Flood") and wet roads killed two people in traffic accidents. Rough seas killed one [surfer](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surfing "Surfing") in Pinellas County, Florida. In Florida and [Georgia](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Georgia_\(U.S._state\) "Georgia \(U.S. state\)"), the rain helped [firefighters](https://simple.wikipedia.org/wiki/Firefighter "Firefighter") fight [wildfires](https://simple.wiktionary.org/wiki/wildfire "wikt:wildfire"). Damage from the storm was minor.

## About Wikipedia
This is the front page of the **Simple English Wikipedia⟨46⟩**. _Wikipedias_ are places where people work together to write encyclopedias⟨43⟩ in different languages. We use Simple English⟨51⟩ words and grammar⟨52⟩ here. The Simple English Wikipedia is for everyone, such as children and adults who are learning English. They have all been published under both the _Creative Commons Attribution/Share-Alike License 4.0 International License⟨54⟩_ and the _GNU Free Documentation License⟨55⟩_. **You can help here!** You may change these pages and make new pages. When writing articles here: 
  * **UseBasic English⟨58⟩ words and shorter sentences.** This allows people to understand complex terms or phrases.
  * **Write good pages.** The best encyclopedia pages have useful, well-written information.
  * **Use the pages to learn and teach.** These pages can help people learn English. You can also use them to make a new Wikipedia⟨59⟩ to help other people.
  * **Simple does not mean short.** Writing in Simple English means that simple words are used. It does not mean readers want basic information. Articles do not have to be short to be simple; expand articles, add details, but use basic vocabulary⟨60⟩.
  * **Be bold!** Your article does not have to be perfect, because other editors will fix it and make it better. And most importantly, do not be afraid to start and make articles better yourself.
